ne 11, 2020). Latest issue consulted: Volume 23, number 166 (July 31, 1897) (Chroniclingamerica.loc.gov, viewed June 11, 2020). Age-herald 2692-4102 (DLC) 2020271954 (OCoLC)664149721"], "digitized": true, "extract_timestamp": "2026-05-19T21:37:52.256Z", "group": ["ndnp/newspapers", "united-states-newspaper-directory"], "hassegments": false, "id": "http://www.loc.gov/item/2020271956/", "image_url": [], "index": 13, "language": ["english"], "location": ["birmingham", "alabama", "jefferson", "united states"], "number": ["2692-4269", "2020271954", "online resource", "2026-04-13t21:30:13", "2020271955", "1157347560", "2020271956"], "original_format": ["newspaper"], "partof": ["serial and government publications division", "birmingham state herald (birmingham, ala.) 1895-1897 [online resource]", "directory of u.s. newspapers in american libraries"], "publication_frequency": ["daily"], "score": 43.808174, "shelf_id": "ISSN RECORD", "site": ["usnd"], "subject": ["united states", "birmingham", "newspapers", "alabama", "jefferson", "birmingham (ala.)"], "timestamp": "2026-05-26T21:01:07.415Z", "title": "Birmingham state herald", "type": ["title"], "url": "https://www.loc.gov/item/2020271956/"}, {"access_restricted": false, "aka": ["http://www.loc.gov/item/2020271957/"], "campaigns": [], "date": "1902", "dates": ["[1902 TO 1950]"], "description": ["Daily Began with vol. 28, no. 330 (May 21, 1902); ceased May 13, 1950. Publication suspended with July 12, 1945 issue due to a printers' strike; resumed publication with Aug. 17, 1945 issue. Also issued on microfilm from Bell & Howell, Micro Photo Div.; the Library of Congress, Photoduplication Service. Also published in a weekly ed. Description based on: Vol. 28, No. 330 (May 21, 1902); title from masthead (Chroniclingamerica.loc.gov, viewed June 25, 2020). Latest issue consulted: Vol. 32, No. 200 (November 16, 1905) (Chroniclingamerica.loc.gov, viewed June 25, 2020). Birmingham post Birmingham post-herald"], "digitized": true, "ex